    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Upholstered fiberglass-shell armchairs designed by Joe Colombo in 1964 and manufactured by Comfort Italy from 1965. The 'Elda 1005' is considered to be the first large armchair made out of fiberglass. A large self-supporting shell rotates on a base, the inside of which is upholstered in leather.</Note_Text>
